P(\text{Not improving})
P(\text{Improving})=1-P(\text{Not improving})
 P(\text{First card won't give you trips}) = \frac{45}{47} 
 P(\text{Second card won't give trips or two pairs}) = \frac{41}{46} 
2 + 3 + 3
 P(\text{last card won't give trips or two pairs}) = \frac{37}{45}  
 P(\text{Not improved}) = \frac{45}{47} \cdot \frac{41}{46} \cdot \frac{37}{45} \approx 0.702 
 P(\text{Improved}) \approx 0.298. 
\approx 1\%
